civics.name: Constitutional Law: Alligator Protection
civics.description: Because of the constitutional referendum, alligators will now be protected because of their allegedly bugged status. They are a lot worse at surviving than all other species and go extinct really fast, so the government usually has no time to protect them properly. Once alligators are confirmed to be fixed and in line with the other species, this law can be abolished again.

properties.Title: Alligator Protection
properties.UserDescription: Prevent the hunting of alligators if their population is less than or equal to 50.

properties.Title: Starting Election Regulations
properties.UserDescription:
Elections may only be started on day 1, 8, 15, 22 and 29. In case an office is vacant, Game Masters may start an election immediately. The term of that official will end on the next regular election day.
This means, in code, that elections may only be started if the world age in days modulo 7 is less than 1. Example: on the middle of world day 15, the world is 14.5 days old. 14.5 mod 7 is 0.5 and therefore less than 1.

civics.name: Wage Regulations
civics.description: Every hour, every member of the government gets a wage according to the index wage. The senate can adjust this index wage by changing the custom stat on the White-Tiger citizen. Wages are paid out of the personal wealth of the White-Tiger citizen so the Government has to make sure to keep this wealth stocked up. Owed wages are tracked. The starting index wage is 100$ per hour.
